explanation:
## Why Asked
Tests understanding of SwiftUI data flow patterns and property wrapper usage in real apps.
## Key Concepts
- @State: Local source of truth for view-owned data
- @Binding: Two-way connection to external state
- @Environment: System-provided or custom app-wide values
## Code Example
```
struct ParentView: View {
    @State private var count = 0
    @Environment(\.colorScheme) var colorScheme

    var body: some View {
        ChildView(count: $count)
    }
}

struct ChildView: View {
    @Binding var count: Int

    var body: some View {
        Button("\(count)") { count += 1 }
    }
}
```
## Follow-up Questions
- When would you use @StateObject instead?
- How does @EnvironmentObject differ from @Environment?
- Can you explain property wrapper composition?
